    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                    ><lang/><w>*čārman-</w><gloss><q>шкура</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ira"><w/><gloss><q>кожа</q></gloss></mentioned>, , c отпадением конечного
        -%ian%i-, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wærm"/> ‘яма’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_casm"/> ‘петля’ и др. Ср.<mentioned xml:lang="ps"
            ><lang/><w>carman</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
            ><lang/><w>čarm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
            ><lang/><w>čarm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"
            ><lang/><w>carm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
            ><lang/><w>*čarn(črm)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
            ><lang/><w>čarman-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>čarman-</w><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope
                        xml:lang="ru">1951, стр. 41</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1951, p.
                        41</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref
                        target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1951, стр.
                        41</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1951, p.
                41</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>čarəman-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>čarman-</w><gloss><q>шкура</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>чрѣмъ</w><gloss><q>шатер</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned
            xml:lang=""><lang/><w>cærmin</w><gloss><q>кожаный</q></gloss></mentioned> — <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>čarmin</w></mentioned>. — О технике обработки кожи у осетин см.
        под словом <ref type="xr" target="#entry_yldyǧ"/>. Нерасчлененность значений ‘шкура’ и
        ‘кожа’ говорит о том, что кожевенное производство не достигло значительного
                развития.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50,
            78</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>18,
                161</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                    ><lang/><w>*čārman-</w><gloss><q>fell</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ira"><w/><gloss><q>skin</q></gloss></mentioned>, , with the loss of the final
        -%ian%i-, like in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wærm"/> ‘hole’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_casm"/> ‘loop’ etc. Cf.<mentioned xml:lang="ps"
            ><lang/><w>carman</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
            ><lang/><w>čarm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
            ><lang/><w>čarm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"
            ><lang/><w>carm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
            ><lang/><w>*čarn(črm)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
            ><lang/><w>čarman-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>čarman-</w><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope
                        xml:lang="ru">1951, стр. 41</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1951, p.
                        41</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref
                        target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1951, стр.
                        41</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1951, p.
                41</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>čarəman-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>čarman-</w><gloss><q>fell</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>črěmъ</w><gloss><q>tent</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned
            xml:lang=""><lang/><w>cærmin</w><gloss><q>(made of) leather</q></gloss></mentioned> —
            <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>čarmin</w></mentioned>. — See the word <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_yldyǧ"/> for the technique of leather working in Ossetia . The
        indivisibility of meanings ‘fell’ and ‘skin’ shows that leathermaking has not reached
        significant development.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50,
                78</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>18,
                161</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
